snippet.textDisplay: To all those haters out there dissing the authorities on this matter, they have a legal, ethical and responsible duty of care to follow. How would you feel if he went missing and the USCG just didn't bother intervening in the first place? There would be an element of uproar and discontent stating they were derelict in their duty. Bubble man needed his bubble to be burst and brought back to reality as he was operating outside of normal reasoning and common sense. The only action I disagree with was that all his personal belongings were destroyed in the process (GPS, laptop etc) as they should have allowed him to retain those. But furthermore the bubble was definitely a navigational hazard to other vessels transiting in the region as there could have been a potential for him to be killed too. He should have just stuck to using a boat or yacht instead!
